b'UNIQLO is releasing Issue 03 of LifeWear Magazine
Issue 03 2020 Fall & Winter
When we began putting together Issue 03 of LifeWear magazine, the idea was to do a feature on sustainability, a theme of the utmost concern to us, as an apparel company. But in the past six months, the entire world has changed. This is no time to preach about sustainability as if it were a passing trend. Instead, we took the opportunity to revisit such vital questions as what matters most to us, how we can be of service, and the meaning of \xe2\x80\x9cessential\xe2\x80\x9d with respect to clothing.
With this mind, we shifted the theme to \xe2\x80\x9cOur Tomorrow\xe2\x80\x9d, and organized the issue around a free discussion of the future

\xef\xbb\xbf It\xe2\x80\x99s a joy to see how a belt transforms over the years. With time, it takes on that character and it all starts with the material. Our exclusive choice is the hide of cows on farms with strict quality management and care.

"A summer conceived from the thread.\xe2\x80\x9d

\xef\xbb\xbf A summer cardigan you throw it over to enjoy the breezy coolness.
This was the concept we embarked on. The key was in the evolution of the thread.
Made by weaving two different material, a soft rayon for the core and double-strand of shiny acetate wraps around it. What you end up is a fabric with a cool touch.
Despite being a delicate material, we\xe2\x80\x99ve introduced one idea after another to make it easy to care with washing machine. As this required a complex weaving technique, our veteran craftsmen went through numerous and meticulous adjustments to the weaving machine. With great care and patience, we came up with this airy light fabric. This is bound to bring great comfort to someone\xe2\x80\x99s summer.

"Combining the wisdom of old and new.\xe2\x80\x9d
\xef\xbb\xbf
Summer in Japan is known for its heat and humidity, which is why past generations invented clothes to help cool you down, like women's RELACO. UNIQLO takes these traditional concepts and updates them for modern times with smart designs in more comfortable materials. For example, we updated the pockets with quick-drying mesh fabric and use cool-touch rayon and cotton for the Women's RELACO styles. The wisdom of the old and new combine to create RELACO.

Refreshing comfort inspired by summers past.

"As many aspirations as there are colors"\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
It's often said that few other brands make as many regular improvements to their classic styles as UNIQLO does, which is certainly true in the case of our chino shorts. This season, we're offering them in 14 different colors, but that's not all that's special. We set out to create a classic vintage look for each color. This led us to scrutinize every stage of production; the level of shrinking has been calculated to the millimeter, not to mention the fine adjustment to the length of time and the temperature in the treatment processes. All this was done to identify the best method to achieve each particular color. With great focus and care, we came to our solutions. The result is truly authentic vintage color. Because there is no shortcut to perfect summer style.\xef\xbb\xbf

\xef\xbb\xbf
Many believe that a standard is something that withstands the test of time. At UNIQLO, we beg to differ. A standard continues to steadily progress. The Pocketable Parka you can fold so small is just one such example. We\xe2\x80\x99ve adjusted the zipper tag so that it\xe2\x80\x99s easy to pinch and pull out of your bag quickly. A three-dimensional hood design wraps around the top, back, and sides of your head. The mesh inside the pocket keeps you from overheating. The lining is positioned to give the best possible comfort around the arms. Every year, the fit is refined by just millimeters. All so that you can quickly put it on when you need to. There is no end to progress. Not ever.\xef\xbb\xbf

b'A Message to Our UNIQLO Community\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
Our priority during these challenging times is the health and safety of our customers, employees and communities around the world.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
To help combat the spread of COVID-19, UNIQLO parent company Fast Retailing has enlisted the support of its manufacturing partners to procure 10 million masks that will be donated to high-priority medical facilities worldwide. And our aim is to provide more assistance as specific needs become clear.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
At this time, we share our deep respect for the many people who are providing care for those affected.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
We wish you and your family to stay healthy and well.\xef\xbb\xbf

b'We are deeply saddened by the passing of our good friend and collaborator @jasonpolan .\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
Jason was an exceptionally talented artist and a genuinely kind person.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
He had the rare gift of making the most everyday things beautiful and interesting.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
It was an extension of the way he lived his life.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
We extend our deepest condolences to his family and friends.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
Thank you, Jason. We will miss you dearly.\xef\xbb\xbf
\xef\xbb\xbf
In 2016, Jason visited Tokyo for the first time to work on his first collection with UNIQLO. These are some of the scans of his drawings that eventually became products that people were able to enjoy around the globe\xef\xbb\xbf.
\xef\xbb\xbf
It has been our honor to have worked with him on numerous special collections from 2016 to 2019 featuring his original art inspired by New York, Japan and his love of Marvel.'
